# Agent Instructions — Nibana

Nibana is Kapil Gupta's private, 1:1 coaching practice for people who look successful on the outside but feel disconnected, flat, or stuck underneath — the feeling of "I've done everything I was told would make me happy, so why isn't it enough?" The work moves people from performance (proving, achieving, managing how they're seen) to presence (direct contact with their own life). All coaching is private, global, and conducted over Zoom. Nibana is not a product store — there is no cart, catalog, or checkout on this site.

## Who this is for

Nibana works with founders, executives, senior leaders, couples, and individuals who have already achieved real success — the job, the business, the relationship, the status — and still feel something is missing. Common ways people describe what brought them here:

- "I've ticked the boxes, so why am I not happy?"
- Feeling successful but empty, flat, or secretly lost
- Burnout that isn't about workload — it's about disconnection
- Repeating the same patterns in relationships or leadership despite trying to change
- Feeling like life looks good on paper but doesn't feel alive from the inside
- Wanting deeper intimacy, purpose, or connection but not knowing what's actually missing

Not a fit: people wanting quick tactics without doing real personal work, or people needing clinical treatment for an acute mental health crisis (Nibana will refer out in that case).

## What Nibana actually does

Nibana helps clients see and work with the unconscious patterns keeping them disconnected from aliveness, intimacy, purpose, and freedom — through coaching conversations, identity work, embodied practice, and integration into real life (not just insight in a session). The throughline across every offer is the same shift: from performance (proving, controlling, managing how you're seen) to presence (direct participation in your own life).

What changes for clients: they stop needing every achievement, relationship, or outcome to prove they're enough. They become more able to stay present in hard conversations, more connected to their body and what they actually want (versus what they've been told to want), and more able to enjoy what they've built instead of only using it as a platform for the next thing.

